#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:2
msgid "cmake_diagnostic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:6
msgid ""
"Manage CMake Diagnostic settings.  See the :manual:`cmake-diagnostics(7)` "
"manual for a list of available categories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:10
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:14
msgid ""
"`Setting Diagnostics`_\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(`SET`_ <category> <action> [RECURSE])\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(`PROMOTE`_ <category> <action> [NO_RECURSE])\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(`DEMOTE`_ <category> <action> [NO_RECURSE])\n"
"\n"
"`Checking Diagnostic Actions`_\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(`GET`_ <diagnostic> <out-var>)\n"
"\n"
"`CMake Diagnostic Stack`_\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(`PUSH`_)\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(`POP`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:27
msgid "Setting Diagnostics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:38
msgid ""
"Set or alter the action taken when a diagnostic belonging to a particular "
"category is triggered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:41
msgid ""
"The ``SET`` subcommand sets the action for the specified diagnostic "
"category. The ``PROMOTE`` subcommand increases the severity for the "
"specified diagnostic category, or does nothing if the action was already set "
"to an equal or higher severity.  The ``DEMOTE`` subcommand decreases the "
"severity for the specified diagnostic category, or does nothing if the "
"action was already set to an equal or lower severity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:48
msgid "The possible ``<action>``\\ s (in order of severity) are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:50
msgid "``IGNORE``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:51
msgid "Do nothing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:53
msgid "``WARN``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:54
msgid "Report a warning and continue processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:56
msgid "``SEND_ERROR``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:57
msgid "Report an error, continue processing, but skip generation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:59
#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:65
msgid ""
"The :manual:`cmake(1)` executable will return a non-zero :ref:`exit code "
"<CMake Exit Code>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:62
msgid "``FATAL_ERROR``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:63
msgid "Report an error, stop processing and generation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:68
msgid ""
"Some diagnostic categories are hierarchical.  The ``RECURSE`` and "
"``NO_RECURSE`` options determine whether changing the action for a "
"diagnostic category also modifies any child categories.  By default, the "
"``PROMOTE`` and ``DEMOTE`` subcommands are recursive, while the ``SET`` "
"subcommand is not. Note that the alteration for child categories is "
"independent of the prior action set on any parents; that is, ``PROMOTE`` and "
"``DEMOTE``, when operating recursively, will operate on all child categories "
"even if a parent category's action was not altered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:78
msgid "Checking Diagnostic Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:83
msgid ""
"Check what action is currently specified for a diagnostic category. The "
"output ``<variable>`` value will be one of ``IGNORE``, ``WARN``, "
"``SEND_ERROR`` or ``FATAL_ERROR``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:88
msgid "CMake Diagnostic Stack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:90
msgid ""
"CMake keeps diagnostic settings on a stack, so changes made by the "
"``cmake_diagnostic`` command affect only the top of the stack.  A new entry "
"on the diagnostic stack is managed automatically for each subdirectory to "
"protect its parents and siblings.  CMake also manages a new entry for "
"scripts loaded by :command:`include` and :command:`find_package` commands "
"except when invoked with the ``NO_DIAGNOSTIC_SCOPE`` option.  The "
"``cmake_diagnostic`` command provides an interface to manage custom entries "
"on the diagnostic stack:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:100
msgid "Create a new entry on the diagnostic stack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:104
msgid ""
"Remove the last diagnostic stack entry created with "
"``cmake_diagnostic(PUSH)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:107
msgid ""
"Each ``PUSH`` must have a matching ``POP`` to erase any changes. This is "
"useful to make temporary changes to diagnostic settings. Calls to the :"
"command:`cmake_diagnostic(SET)`, :command:`cmake_diagnostic(PROMOTE)`, or :"
"command:`cmake_diagnostic(DEMOTE)` commands influence only the current top "
"of the diagnostic stack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:113
msgid ""
"The :command:`block(SCOPE_FOR DIAGNOSTICS)` command offers a more flexible "
"and more secure way to manage the diagnostic stack. The pop action is done "
"automatically when leaving the block scope, so there is no need to precede "
"each :command:`return` with a call to :command:`cmake_diagnostic(POP)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:118
msgid ""
"# stack management with cmake_diagnostic()\n"
"function(my_func)\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(PUSH)\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(SET ...)\n"
"  if (<cond1>)\n"
"    ...\n"
"    cmake_diagnostic(POP)\n"
"    return()\n"
"  elseif(<cond2>)\n"
"    ...\n"
"    cmake_diagnostic(POP)\n"
"    return()\n"
"  endif()\n"
"  ...\n"
"  cmake_diagnostic(POP)\n"
"endfunction()\n"
"\n"
"# stack management with block()/endblock()\n"
"function(my_func)\n"
"  block(SCOPE_FOR DIAGNOSTICS)\n"
"    cmake_diagnostic(SET ...)\n"
"    if (<cond1>)\n"
"      ...\n"
"      return()\n"
"    elseif(<cond2>)\n"
"      ...\n"
"      return()\n"
"    endif()\n"
"    ...\n"
"  endblock()\n"
"endfunction()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../command/cmake_diagnostic.rst:152
msgid ""
"Commands created by the :command:`function` and :command:`macro` commands "
"record diagnostic settings when they are created and use the pre-record "
"diagnostics when they are invoked.  If the function or macro implementation "
"sets diagnostics, the changes automatically propagate up through callers "
"until they reach the closest nested diagnostic stack entry."
msgstr ""
